# Mothman Branding

Applies when generating **externally shareable or copy-paste-ready work artifacts**
— HTML pages, PDFs, Excel workbooks, slide decks, formatted reports, and
browser-preview drafts for Outlook or Teams.

Identity, tone, and outbound signing live in sibling rules:

- `.cursor/rules/agent-identity.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/outbound-messaging-guardrail.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/teams-dm-formatting.mdc`

This rule covers **visual presentation and corporate identity only**.

## Workspace name

**Mothman** is this repository's internal codename. Do **not** use "Mothman" in
customer-facing copy, email bodies, ticket replies, or leadership comms. External
artifacts carry **Vixxo** branding only.

## Vixxo color palette

Use these hex values for charts, headers, accents, and styled exports:

| Token | Hex | Use |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Primary** | `#2C7B80` | Headings, key accents, chart series 1 |
| **Accent** | `#FAB000` | Highlights, callouts, chart series 2 |
| **Secondary** | `#8E992E` | Supporting accents, chart series 3 |
| **Text** | `#3E4543` | Body copy on light backgrounds |
| **Muted** | `#666666` | Captions, footnotes, secondary labels |
| **Link** | `#0563C1` | Hyperlinks (Office/PDF convention) |
| **Background** | `#FFFFFF` | Page and email body background |
| **Header fill** | `#D9E1F2` | Excel/table header rows (light blue-gray) |

Do not invent alternate brand colors. Do not use Cursor's dark-theme palette in
artifacts meant for Outlook, Teams, PDF, or print.

## Typography

| Surface | Font | Size | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Outlook / Word / Excel** | Calibri | 11pt body; 14pt section titles | Matches Vixxo email defaults |
| **HTML browser preview** | `Calibri, Arial, sans-serif` | 11pt body | White `#fff` background always |
| **PDF body** | Helvetica or Calibri equivalent | 10–11pt | Dark text on white |
| **Monospace (data only)** | `Consolas, monospace` | 10pt | IDs, JSON, CLI output in reports |

Avoid decorative fonts, all-caps section headers, and heading tags that Outlook
strips or restyles.

## Corporate identity block

When a formal footer, letterhead, or certificate-holder block is required, use
the canonical Vixxo legal identity:

```
Vixxo Corporation
7580 N. Dobson Road, Suite 201
Scottsdale, AZ 85256
```

Use the full legal name **Vixxo Corporation** on first reference in formal
documents; **Vixxo** is acceptable in running prose after that.

Do not embed or fabricate logo image files. If a logo is required and no
approved asset is available in the workspace, leave a text header and note the
gap for {{employee_name}}.

## HTML and Outlook constraints

Follow the same constraints as the `outlook-email-formatter` skill:

- Inline styles only — no `<style>` blocks or external stylesheets
- Background `#fff`; body text `#000` or `#3E4543`
- Links: `<a href="url">label</a>` or `color="#0563C1"` with underline for PDF
- No emojis unless {{employee_name}} included them in the source draft

## Excel and tabular exports

When generating `.xlsx` reports programmatically:

- Header row: fill `#D9E1F2`, bold black 11pt, centered, wrapped
- Data cells: Calibri 11pt, `#000000`, top-aligned, wrap enabled
- Hyperlinks: `#0563C1`, underlined
- Thin borders on data tables
- Sheet titles: bold 14pt in cell A1 when a cover row is needed

## PDF exports

- White page background; dark body text
- Hyperlinks: `#0563C1` with underline
- Page margins suitable for print (≥ 0.5 in)
- Include document title and generation date in header or footer when the report
  will be archived or shared externally

## Voice and signing

- **Drafted in {{employee_name}}'s voice:** no AI sign-off; reads as their words
  (see outbound-messaging guardrail).
- **Teams AI-assisted posts:** follow the inline sign-off in
  `outbound-messaging-guardrail.mdc` — not "Mothman", not a mascot name.
- **Email:** no AI sign-off; {{employee_name}}'s Outlook signature handles it.

## Prohibited branding

- "Mothman", mascot imagery, or folklore references in external artifacts
- "AI transformation", "AI platform", or generic chatbot branding in Vixxo comms
- Dark-background HTML copied from the Cursor chat UI
- Unofficial colors, gradients, or stock imagery presented as Vixxo brand
- Fabricated logos, taglines, or trademark symbols (®, ™) not sourced from
  approved Vixxo materials

